The paper discusses the architecture and application characteristics of Edge, Fog, and Cloud computing in the context of IoT. This makes it likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses networking and communication aspects, making it relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses platform abstractions and runtime environments, making it relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses challenges and gaps in the current implementation of Fog computing, making it relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses privacy sensitivity, making it relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
